        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Please correct me if I'm wrong in my recent observations.</P><P>With the possible new focii items coming into the game, does the mean that necro dmg has once AGAIN been indirectly nerfed ?<BR>Let's see, we do not benefit from<ul><li>Spell Casting Fury</li><li>Magician summoned focus items</li><li>Pending Improved Damage dropped focii items</li></ul>Will all of the above stack ?  I also play a wizard, will her innate chance to crit stack also ?</P><P>The affliction line is a JOKE, and no where near compensates the possible damage increases with the DD line of spells, which the necro class has a poor arsenal.</P><P>I'm begining to wonder if all these recent impacts on the necro class have been instigated from another class.<BR><ul><li>pets - mages have argued for changes a long time, oh wait the spec pet was BUGGED anyway and needed fixing.</li><li>focus stuff - casters all want to deal more dmg, hell they even introduced 1k ish DDs for clerics, druids and enchanters</li><li>Lich - well to be fair with the introduction of KEI our margin of mana regen was diminished.  Oh wait, AL was bugged and needed FIXING.</li></ul>I am sure there are more .. please add.</P><P>I do welcome these much needed changes we have witnessed recently.  However, I feel that NONE of them have addressed the necro needs directly.  Our damage is via DoTs - for pity's sake, let us increase the DPS.  I am still waiting for a NECRO ENHANCEMENT.</P><P>Lamah Pujahama, The Nameless</P><P>-edit-<BR>typo's and final comment <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>Edited by - toothless on 06/04/2002  15:11:31</font></td>

