        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I think what msot people means is that extended duration does not help necros because we seldom if ever run out of mana anyways.  Thus, it is the same DPS over time.  Thus, though soloing wise it would be more efficient (you'd need to cast less DoTs than before), on raids it is of minimal significance since you'd be doing the same damage over time.</P><P>An example:</P><P>You cast Funeral Pyre 10 times on a raid, doing 20k damage.</P><P>With focus items, you cast it only 8 times, doing also 20k damage.  </P><P>However, since the duration of the focused DoTs are longer and DoTs don't stack with themselves, you're doing 20k damage in the same time period as before.</P><P>It would have been much better if DoT damage were improved across the board by focus items, but that's not always possible, just like DoT stacking is not always possible.</P><P></P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

